# Gen.UI.Audit

A lightweight, portable UI audit framework that combines Playwright browser automation with Yumlog screen capture capabilities for comprehensive UI validation.

## Features

- **Multi-browser testing**: Chromium, Firefox, and WebKit support
- **Visual regression**: Screenshot comparison and baseline management
- **PowerShell integration**: Native Windows automation with Skills modules
- **Flexible configuration**: JSON-based configuration system
- **Comprehensive reports**: HTML reports with detailed test results
- **Screen recording**: Optional Yumlog integration for session recording
- **Test templates**: Ready-to-use templates for common UI patterns

## Installation

After Chocolatey installation, the framework will be available at:
`C:\ProgramData\Gen.UI.Audit\`

## Quick Start

```powershell
# Navigate to installation directory
cd C:\ProgramData\Gen.UI.Audit

# Install Node dependencies (first time only)
npm install

# Install Playwright browsers (first time only)
npx playwright install chromium

# Run a basic audit
.\launchers\audit-ui.ps1 -Target ".\your-app.html"
```

## Dependencies

- PowerShell 5.1+ or PowerShell Core 7+
- Node.js 16+ (installed automatically by Chocolatey)
- FFmpeg (optional, for Yumlog screen capture)

## Documentation

- **README**: Complete framework documentation
- **API Reference**: Detailed command reference
- **Quick Start Guide**: Get started in minutes
- **Test Templates**: Reusable test patterns

